[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer run on the Mongoose codebase triggered an AddressSanitizer [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow in the function `rx_icmp` within `src/net_builtin.c`. The [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer log shows a one-byte read occurring just past the end of a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation. The overflow is detected when processing a fuzzed ICMP packet via the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTCP/IP receive path.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  During a fuzz campaign with AddressSanitizer enabled, the fuzzer invoked [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `src/mongoose/test/fuzz.c`, which in turn called into [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe Mongoose TCP/IP stack. While handling a crafted packet, `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_tcpip_if*, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` performed a read access one byte beyond the end of a dynamically allocated [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability type  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Heap-buffer-overflow: a read of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at an address immediately after a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap allocation.[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Key observations  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The overflow occurs in `rx_icmp` at net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385:18[0m[39m.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The corrupted address [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past the [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x150[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x172[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m allocated earlier in the call stack.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The allocation happens in the fuzz entry point [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`fuzz.c` at line [0m[1;36m95[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, likely by creating a `pkt` structure or its payload.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The call chain is: LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput → mg_tcpip_rx [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`net_builtin.c`:[0m[1;36m897[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m →[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrx_icmp [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`net_builtin.c`:[0m[1;36m385[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • AddressSanitizer’s shadow memory dump confirms the read touches a “heap left [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mredzone” byte.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Relevant code areas to inspect  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Function `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_tcpip_if*, pkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` around line [0m[1;36m385[0m[39m in [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/net_builtin.c`—check bounds checks and packet parsing logic.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. The TCP/IP receive dispatcher `mg_tcpip_rx` in `src/net_builtin.c` around line[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m897[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The test harness in `src/mongoose/test/fuzz.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlines [0m[1;36m95[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m106[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, which allocates[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand feeds the packet to the stack.  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Definitions and allocation logic for the `pkt` structure or its payload [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer, to understand how its size is determined.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m5[0m[39m. Any helper routines that compute or validate packet length fields before [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mslicing or indexing into the payload.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-v [0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpare_bued[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue arises when running the libFuzzer harness against the `rx_icmp` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction in `src/net_builtin.c`: AddressSanitizer reports a one-byte [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow on `pkt->icmp->type` at line [0m[1;36m385[0m[39m. A patch was attempted that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madds an early return guard checking `pkt->raw.len` against the combined sizes of [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe Ethernet, IP, and ICMP headers before accessing `pkt->icmp`. Despite this [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange, the overflow persists in the same location and under the same conditions [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen re-running the fuzzer.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer invokes `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, which allocates a `pkt` buffer [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbased on the input length.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Inside `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_tcpip_if *ifp, struct pkt *pkt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, the code [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimmediately dereferences `pkt->icmp->type` and `pkt->ip->dst` without verifying [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat the buffer contains a complete ICMP header.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer flags a heap-buffer-overflow reading one byte just past the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mend of a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte allocation, indicating that the code underestimates the minimum [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpacket length required for safe access.[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations from the Initial Log  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Crash location: `[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mnet_builtin.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m385:18[0m[39m` in `rx_icmp`.  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The offending address is at offset [0m[1;36m0x22[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m34[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from the base of a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocation.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs on the first byte of the ICMP header.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The heap allocation is performed in the fuzz harness [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m with no further length checks before calling [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_tcpip_rx` → `rx_icmp`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Modifications in `src/net_builtin.c` around `rx_icmp`:  [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -static void [0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_tcpip_if *ifp, struct pkt *pkt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -  if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && pkt->ip != NULL && pkt->ip->dst == ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +static void [0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_tcpip_if *ifp, struct pkt *pkt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->raw.len < [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39micmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+      return;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && pkt->ip != NULL && pkt->ip->dst == ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         size_t hlen = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39micmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[33m...[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The guard tests `pkt->raw.len` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtotal raw packet length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m against a constant [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msum of header sizes and returns early if the packet is too short.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result After Patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer is rerun with the same harness and test case.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer still reports a heap-buffer-overflow at the same line [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`rx_icmp:[0m[1;92m385:18[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow address and allocation size remain unchanged, indicating the new [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard did not prevent the out-of-bounds read.[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verification of `pkt->raw.len` vs. the actual offset of `pkt->icmp` within the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer. Ensure that `raw.len` covers the Ethernet header, IP header, and any IP [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader options that affect header length.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Calculation of `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` vs. the on-wire IP header length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ihl` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfield[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m — malformed or truncated IP headers could make fixed-size checks [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minsufficient.  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definitions and alignment of `struct eth`, `struct ip`, `struct icmp`, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe layout of `struct pkt` to confirm that the offsets match expectations.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How `mg_tcpip_rx` dispatches to `rx_icmp` and what invariants it assumes about[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer length and validity before calling it.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additional checks that account for variable ICMP payload lengths and dynamic [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader sizes may be necessary to fully prevent out-of-bounds accesses.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a one-byte heap-buffer-overflow detected by AddressSanitizer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnet_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing a fuzzed packet. A patch was [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplied to recompute the IP header length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ihl`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, reposition the ICMP header [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpointer inside the raw buffer, and add checks against `raw.len` before invoking [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mmkpay[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. After rebuilding and re-running the fuzzer, the same buffer overflow in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` was observed at the identical location, indicating the patch did not [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mprevent the out-of-bounds read.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - An AddressSanitizer error reports a heap-buffer-overflow in function [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mmg_tcpip_if*, pkt*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` at net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failing read is size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at address `[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[39m`, exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap allocation.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs on `pkt->icmp->type` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe first byte of the ICMP header[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen `pkt->icmp` is computed as `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp *[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->ip + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Call stack excerpt:  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mmg_tcpip_rx[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:897[0m[39m  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. `[0m[1;35mLLVMFuzzerTestOneInput[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` in test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:106[0m[39m  [0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Fuzzer loop in `FuzzerLoop.cpp` and `FuzzerDriver.cpp`  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Observations from Initial Log  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The raw packet buffer is [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m bytes long [0m[1;39m([0m[39mheap-allocated via `malloc`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No check ensures that the ICMP header lies entirely within the allocated [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mregion.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The simplistic calculation `pkt->icmp = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp *[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->ip + [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` assumes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma fixed IP header size, but real packets can have variable header lengths.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Wrapped the ICMP‐handling branch in an inner block.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Computed `size_t ihl = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->ip->hlen & [0m[1;36m0x0f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m;` to derive the IP header [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlength from the `ihl` field.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added a raw‐buffer length check:  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Ensure `pkt->raw.len >= [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + ihl + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Repositioned `pkt->icmp = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp *[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39muint8_t *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->ip + ihl[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Verified that `[0m[1;39m([0m[39muint8_t *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->icmp + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*pkt->icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` does not exceed [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end of `pkt->raw.buf + pkt->raw.len`.  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Adjusted `[0m[1;35mmkpay[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call to use the new ICMP offset.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Post-Patch Result  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer output shows the same AddressSanitizer one-byte overflow at [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnet_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The backtrace and allocated region size remain identical.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This indicates that the new bounds checks do not prevent the code path leading[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto the out-of-bounds read.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic in `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` around packet length and offset calculations, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluding edge conditions when `pkt->raw.len` is exactly the sum of expected header[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msizes.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Definitions and use of `pkt->raw.len` vs. `pkt->pay.len`, and the interaction [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbetween `[0m[1;35mmkpay[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and subsequent buffer accesses.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The `[0m[1;35mmkpay[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` function itself, to confirm it correctly sets `pkt->pay.buf` and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`pkt->pay.len` in all cases.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Possible interactions with fragmentation handling earlier in `[0m[1;35mmg_tcpip_rx[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The structure layouts for `struct eth`, `struct ip`, `struct icmp`, and their [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malignment/padding.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m---  [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo root‐cause speculation or fixes beyond those attempted are included. This report[0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Initial issue: AddressSanitizer detected a heap-buffer-overflow in `rx_icmp` [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mnet_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when fuzzing the Mongoose network code. The crash occurs on a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread of `pkt->icmp->type`, one byte past the end of a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap buffer.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patch attempt: The `rx_icmp` function was rewritten to add early returns that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidate `pkt->ip`, the raw buffer length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->raw.len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the IPv4 header length [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`ihl`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, and ensure the ICMP header fits before assigning `pkt->icmp`. The original[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mICMP-echo-reply logic was intended to be guarded by these checks.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Patch result: The same heap-buffer-overflow in `rx_icmp` persists with an [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentical ASan stack trace at line [0m[1;36m385[0m[39m, indicating the added checks did not prevent[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe overflow.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A fuzzer run produced:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow on read of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m in `rx_icmp` at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnet_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The read address is [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m bytes past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap region [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m150[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m0x[0m[39m…[0m[1;36m172[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Stack trace highlights `rx_icmp`, then `mg_tcpip_rx`, then the fuzz harness [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and libFuzzer internals.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The vulnerable line reads `pkt->icmp->type` before any bounds check on the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation of `pkt->icmp`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mObservations in the initial issue  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `pkt->icmp` points into the raw packet buffer without validation of the buffer’s [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mactual length or the IP header’s IHL.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The raw buffer in this test case was only [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m bytes, too small to contain a full [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEthernet + IP + ICMP header, yet the code proceeds to dereference `pkt->icmp`.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `net_builtin.c`, around line [0m[1;36m380[0m[39m, the old block:[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && pkt->ip != NULL && pkt->ip->dst == ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      … [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m original echo-reply code[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  was replaced with:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->ip == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->raw.len < [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    size_t ihl = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->ip->hlen & [0m[1;36m0x0f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mihl < [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    uint8_t *icmp_start = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint8_t *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->ip + ihl;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39muint8_t *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mpkt->raw.buf + pkt->raw.len[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        < icmp_start + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39m*pkt->icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    pkt->icmp = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39micmp_start;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && pkt->ip->dst == ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      … [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39msupposed to mirror original code[0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    ```[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The new guards check for:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Non-NULL IP pointer.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Raw buffer large enough for Ethernet + minimal IP header.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Valid IHL [0m[1;39m([0m[39mheader length ≥ `[0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. ICMP header wholly inside the raw buffer.[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- If any check fails, the function returns early; otherwise it sets `pkt->icmp` and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtests `pkt->icmp->type`.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mLog after patch  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Running the same fuzz testcase still triggers:[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - heap-buffer-overflow in `rx_icmp` at net_builtin.[0m[1;92mc:385[0m[39m.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The ASan output and stack trace are identical to the initial issue.[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This indicates that the added early returns did not actually prevent the OOB read[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the failing testcase.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Poisoned by user:        f7[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Container overflow:      fc[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Array cookie:            ac[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Intra object redzone:    bb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  ASan internal:           fe[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Left alloca redzone:     ca[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/aixcc/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-v [0m[35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpare_bued[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is an AddressSanitizer-detected heap-buffer-overflow in the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction `rx_icmp` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdefined in `src/net_builtin.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing ICMP echo [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequests in the Mongoose TCP/IP stack under fuzzing. The overflow occurs on a [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read immediately past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte heap allocation, crashing inside `rx_icmp` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat line [0m[1;36m385[0m[39m.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn attempted patch adds:[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Early returns if the packet is too short to contain Ethernet, IP or ICMP headers.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Dynamic extraction of IP header length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ihl`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m from the IPv4 header and [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvalidation against the raw packet length.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A recalculated pointer for `pkt->icmp` based on `ihl`.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Adjusted payload bounds checks for both receive [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`pkt->raw.len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and transmit [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`ifp->tx.len`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m buffers.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the same overflow is still triggered at the same [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation, indicating that the added length checks did not prevent the out-of-bounds[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Crash Type: `ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow`  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Location: `[0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mnet_builtin.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m385:18[0m[39m` in `static void [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_tcpip_if *ifp, struct pkt *pkt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack Trace Highlights:  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `[0m[1;35mmg_tcpip_rx[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Faulting Access: [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read at address `[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[39m`, which is exactly [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes past a [0m[1;36m34[0m[39m-byte region [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x504000000150[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m allocated just [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbefore the crash in `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Context: The fuzzer harness allocates a `pkt` buffer via `malloc`, initializes[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheaders directly from input, and then calls `[0m[1;35mmg_tcpip_rx[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` which dispatches to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`[0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`. The overflowing access reads one byte beyond the allocated region when[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maccessing `pkt->icmp->type` or following ICMP payload.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Important Observations**  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The vulnerable code assumes fixed header sizes:  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m && pkt->ip != NULL && pkt->ip->dst == ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       size_t hlen = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       size_t space = ifp->tx.len - hlen, plen = pkt->pay.len;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mplen > space[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m plen = space;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       …[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No checks against `pkt->pay.buf` or total raw packet length appear before [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdereferencing `pkt->icmp`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer-driven packet can be shorter than expected, leading to [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow when reading `icmp->type`.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The patch replaces the original `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type == [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m …[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` block with the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfollowing [0m[1;39m([0m[39mabridged[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m logic:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```diff[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   static void [0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct mg_tcpip_if *ifp, struct pkt *pkt[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Validate presence of IPv4 header *[0m[35m/[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->ip == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure raw buffer contains Ethernet + minimal IPv4 header *[0m[35m/[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->raw.len < [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Compute IPv4 header length from IHL field *[0m[35m/[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     struct ip *rx_ip_hdr = pkt->ip;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t ihl = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mrx_ip_hdr->hlen & [0m[1;36m0x0f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mihl < [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ||[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         pkt->raw.len < [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + ihl + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       return;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Point to ICMP header safely *[0m[35m/[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     pkt->icmp = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct icmp *[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39muint8_t *[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mrx_ip_hdr + ihl[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Process only echo requests to our IP *[0m[35m/[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpkt->icmp->type != [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m || rx_ip_hdr->dst != ifp->ip[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Bound payload by receive buffer *[0m[35m/[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t max_pay = pkt->raw.len - [0m[1;39m([0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct eth[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + ihl + [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mstruct [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39micmp[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     size_t plen   = pkt->pay.len > max_pay ? max_pay : pkt->pay.len;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     …[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;35mether_output[0m[1;39m([0m[39mifp, hlen + plen[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Early returns guard against `pkt->ip == NULL` and too-small `pkt->raw.len`.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - IP header length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`ihl`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is extracted dynamically and validated.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - ICMP header pointer is recomputed based on `ihl`.[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Payload length [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`plen`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m is capped to both receive and transmit buffer sizes.[0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Patch Result**  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   After rebuilding and rerunning the fuzzer with the patched code, the same [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msanitizer error is reported:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;35mrx_icmp[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m385:18[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   READ of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at [0m[1;36m0x504000000172[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   …[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   SUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mnet_builtin.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m385:18[0m[39m in rx_icmp[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   ```[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The faulting address and allocation region remain identical, meaning the new [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds checks did not fire before the invalid read.[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   To fully understand why the overflow persists, the following code regions and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata structures should be examined:[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Definition and initialization of `struct pkt`, particularly fields `raw.len`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`ip`, `icmp`, and `pay.len` vs `pay.buf`.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer harness in `test/fuzz.c`, to see how it constructs and populates the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpacket buffer.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Function `mg_tcpip_rx`, which sets up `pkt->ip` and other pointers prior to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalling `rx_icmp`.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Memory layout and redzones around the allocated packet buffer, to verify [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether the reported region matches the assumed struct sizes.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Interplay between `pkt->raw.len` and `pkt->pay.len` — the patch uses `raw.len`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor header checks but retains `pay.len` for payload; misalignment could still allow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds reads.[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy auditing these areas, one can build a complete picture of how packet lengths are[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrepresented and enforced, and why the current validation logic in `rx_icmp` still [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallows a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte overflow.[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mfuzz[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ shift[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m [0m[32m'!'[0m[39m -v TESTCASE [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mTESTCASE[0m[39m=[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m [0m[32m'!'[0m[39m -f [0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ export [0m[33mRUN_FUZZER_MODE[0m[39m=[0m[35minteractive[0m                                                [2m                [0m
